There are two very distinct groups from the Cerro del Sira in Huánuco . One has finely pinnate leaves and small inflorescences and occurs at lower elevations (
Dudley 13064, Rainer 133288, 1330188, 2214988, 2314988, Wolfe 12335
); the second ( Rainer 2513988 ) has irregularly pinnate leaves and larger inflorescences, and occurs at higher elevations.
